''See also:'' [[Angst]]
==English==

===Etymology===
From German, a word suggesting fear and tension. Has been adopted into colloquial English.
(In fact its roots are much more ancient. Cf. the Indoeuropean root 'angh-' as in "anxiety" or "anger".)

